<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-14334] DelayedFetch purgatory not completed when appending as follower</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-14334</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, the ReplicaManager.delayedFetchPurgatory is only completed when appending as leader. With &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-392%3A+Allow+consumers+to+fetch+from+closest+replica&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-392%3A+Allow+consumers+to+fetch+from+closest+replica&lt;/a&gt; enabled, followers will also have to complete delayed fetch requests after successfully replicating. Otherwise, consumer fetches to closest followers will hit fetch.max.wait.ms&lt;/p&gt;</description>
